:INFO
The Novel That Required a New Way of Reading
I have started Crime and Punishment three times and failed twice because I tried \
to read it at the pace I read other novels. The third attempt worked because \
I committed to 20 pages a day and nothing more. Dostoevsky's novel about a \
student who murders a pawnbroker and then lives inside the psychological \
aftermath is not a thriller. It is a study in how guilt and rationalization \
coexist in the same mind and the only pace that captures that is a slow one.

